  "Notes": [
    {
      "Text": "Security update for python36",
      "Title": "Topic",
      "Type": "Summary"
    },
    {
      "Text": "This update for python36 fixes the following issues:\n\n- CVE-2025-12084: quadratic complexity when building nested elements using `xml.dom.minidom` methods that depend on\n  `_clear_id_cache()` can lead to availability issues when building excessively nested documents (bsc#1254997).\n- CVE-2025-13836: use of `Content-Length` by default when reading an HTTP response with no read amount specified can\n  lead to OOM issues and DoS when a client deals with a malicious server (bsc#1254400).\n- CVE-2025-13837: data read by the plistlib module according to the size specified by the file itself can lead to OOM\n  issues and DoS (bsc#1254401).\n",
      "Title": "Details",
      "Type": "General"
    },
    {
